textBox.richText: We just got back from Algonquin Park - aside from wiping out badly on the Minesing Mountain Biking trail (which is designed for pros and suicidal idiots only), we managed to see a great deal of Algonquin landscape including its rich variety.  One of our favorite places we found this year is a vast plain of low-lying ferns dotted with the occasional pine - it felt as if we were in Cretaceous North America!
